Deaths Vs. Previous Years

https://www150.statcan.gc.ca/t1/tbl1/en/cv.action?pid=1310078301

# Prep data
dd <- read.csv("1310078301_databaseLoadingData.csv")
colnames(dd)[1] <- "DATE"
dd <- dd %>% mutate(DATE = as.Date(DATE))
xx <- dd %>% 
  group_by(DATE) %>% 
  summarise(VALUE = sum(VALUE, na.rm = T)) %>% 
  mutate(GEO = "Canada")
areas <- c("Canada", "Quebec", "Ontario", "British Columbia", 
           "Alberta", "Saskatchewan", "Manitoba", "Nova Scotia",
           "Newfoundland and Labrador", "New Brunswick", "Prince Edward Island", 
           "Northwest Territories", "Yukon", "Nunavut")
dd <- bind_rows(dd, xx) %>%
  mutate(YEAR = as.factor(substr(DATE, 1, 4)),
         Y2020 = ifelse(YEAR == "2020", "2020", "<2020"),
         JulianDate = lubridate::yday(DATE),
         GEO = gsub(", place of occurrence", "", GEO),
         GEO = factor(GEO, levels = areas))
# Create plotting function
deathPlot <- function(areas) {
  # Prep data
  xx <- dd %>% filter(GEO %in% areas)
  # Plot
  mp1 <- ggplot(xx, aes(x = JulianDate, y = VALUE, group = YEAR, color = Y2020, alpha = Y2020)) +
    geom_line() +
    facet_wrap(GEO ~ ., scales = "free_y", ncol = 5) +
    scale_color_manual(name = NULL, values = c("darkgreen","darkred")) +
    scale_alpha_manual(name = NULL, values = c(0.5,1)) +
    theme_agData(legend.position = "bottom") +
    labs(title = "COVID-19", y = "Deaths Per Week")
  # Prep data
  xx <- dd %>% mutate(YEAR = as.numeric(as.character(YEAR))) %>%
    select(DATE, YEAR, JulianDate, Y2020, GEO, VALUE) %>%
    arrange(GEO, DATE) %>%
    spread(GEO, VALUE)
  for(i in 5:ncol(xx)) {
    for(k in min(xx$YEAR):max(xx$YEAR)) {
      xx[xx$YEAR == k, i] <- cumsum(xx[xx$YEAR == k,i])
    }
  }
  xx <- xx %>% gather(GEO, VALUE, 5:ncol(.)) %>%
    mutate(GEO = factor(GEO, levels = areas)) %>%
    filter(GEO %in% areas)
  # Plot
  mp2 <- ggplot(xx, aes(x = JulianDate, y = VALUE, group = YEAR, color = Y2020, alpha = Y2020)) +
    geom_line() +
    facet_wrap(GEO ~ ., scales = "free_y", ncol = 5) +
    scale_color_manual(name = NULL, values = c("darkgreen","darkred")) +
    scale_alpha_manual(name = NULL, values = c(0.5,1)) +
    theme_agData(legend.position = "bottom") +
    labs(y = "Deaths Per Week(Cummulative)",
         caption = "\xa9 www.dblogr.com/  |  Data: STATCAN")
  ggarrange(mp1, mp2, common.legend = T, legend = "bottom", align = "h")
}

Canada

mp <- deathPlot(areas = areas)
ggsave("Deaths_Canada_01.png", mp, width = 20, height = 8)

mp <- deathPlot(areas = "Canada")
ggsave("Deaths_Canada_02.png", mp, width = 8, height = 4)
